1
00:02:06,001 --> 00:02:10,214
Five soldiers condemned to death were lead to
the sector of Bullavent,

2
00:02:10,297 --> 00:02:12,090
near the Somme River.

3
00:02:40,911 --> 00:02:42,287
The first one was a great adventurer many years before

4
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:48,001
He wore on his neck the number 2124.

5
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,420
He came from a recruitment center of La Seine

6
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:52,214
He was wearing boots

7
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:54,383
He took them from a German soldier.

8
00:02:54,383 --> 00:02:55,717
Before, soldier 2124,

9
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:57,803
called Bastoche

10
00:02:57,803 --> 00:03:00,013
was with a beautiful redhead girl

11
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:02,099
called Véronique Passavant.

12
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:08,188
He was carpenter in the " La Bastille"

13
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:18,282
Sometimes between two furniture pieces

14
00:03:18,282 --> 00:03:23,203
They went to drink a beer in the pub of Petit
Louis on the street "The Golden Hand"

15
00:03:25,581 --> 00:03:28,584
He took the boots from an enemy
who didn't need them any more.

16
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:30,002
in order to replace them,

17
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:35,299
once filled up with straw and newspaper paper,
They replaced his former boots.

18
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:50,606
He went before a military tribunal
for voluntary mutilation.

19
00:03:50,689 --> 00:03:56,403
They found residue of gunpowder in the wound on his
hand, and he was condemned to death.

20
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:20,802
The second soldier wore the number 4077, and
was from another recruitment center of La Seine.

21
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:26,517
He worked on the Steel for the state railroads in
Manille.

22
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:30,604
His name was Francis Ganière, We called him "Six Soux"

23
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:34,191
He knew that the poor
were building the cannons
which will kill them

24
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:36,693
and that the wealthy people sold them.

25
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:42,282
He tried to explain it during
the barrackings, but he didn't explain well.

26
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:47,287
In addition, the cheap wine : their friend in the
misery, made the soldiers so pissed,

27
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:52,709
that he didn't even know how
to interrupt them.

28
00:05:33,292 --> 00:05:36,503
1818 was without any doubt the bravest soldier,

29
00:05:36,587 --> 00:05:38,213
And the most dangerous one.

30
00:05:38,714 --> 00:05:41,592
He once killed the officer of his team.

31
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,804
An officer who hit the dead.

32
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:54,813
Get up ! Get up !

33
00:05:54,813 --> 00:05:59,818
You, go away!

34
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:14,917
No one knew it.

35
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:42,486
Benoît Notre Dame was a farmer.

36
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:49,117
One morning in the month of August,
they went to take him away from his farm,

37
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:52,996
and they forced him on the train.

38
00:07:00,087 --> 00:07:03,090
Be aware of the cables!

39
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:09,513
The phone cables were
the only way to connect to the world of the living.

40
00:07:09,596 --> 00:07:12,891
By that fine thread, they were hoping for
the grace of the president Raymond Poincare
to spare their lives.

41
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,395
Even if the only one here who believed
that was him...

42
00:07:16,520 --> 00:07:20,399
Number 7328,  recruited from
the island of Corsica.

43
00:07:20,482 --> 00:07:23,110
was Ange Bassignano

44
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:29,199
According to all people who knew him,
no one ever had a more unsuitable name.

45
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:33,787
'The Angel' was a liar, a cheater, a fake.

46
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:35,914
An informer and agitator.

47
00:07:46,884 --> 00:07:51,680
Before, he had been the procurer (pimp) of Tina Lombardi

48
00:07:51,889 --> 00:07:56,185
Because of her,
He had been condemned to jail for five years
for an honor or love crime
.

49
00:07:56,185 --> 00:07:58,520
Depending on the whether they
were a woman or a man.

50
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:04,484
Actually... it was a deal
between
the procurers (pimps) of the village.

51
00:08:08,906 --> 00:08:11,909
During the summer of 1916 they recruited
delinquents

52
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:15,120
in order to be able to replace losses within the
massacred regiments

53
00:08:15,287 --> 00:08:18,081
In Berdun hell, it was up to them.

54
00:08:21,585 --> 00:08:23,504
For whom are Those tombs ?

55
00:08:23,587 --> 00:08:28,300
Well Actually... well... as tomorrow they are
going to attack...

56
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:32,596
So we anticipate.

57
00:08:50,781 --> 00:08:53,116
Be aware of the cable.

58
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:04,711
The fifth soldier was a kid who belonged to the section of 17.

59
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:08,715
He just needed 5 months to be 20 years old.

60
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:13,512
And now, he was afraid of everything.

61
00:09:13,512 --> 00:09:15,597
Of the French cannons which were firing so much.

62
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:21,395
Of the wind that spread
the gas of the hunters of robbery, of the executions.

63
00:09:21,603 --> 00:09:24,398
Before the war he was not like this, he was just the
opposite...

64
00:09:24,481 --> 00:09:29,111
He defied storms to help keep lighthouses
working when the tide rose.

65
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:31,613
Charge !!

66
00:09:58,015 --> 00:10:02,811
Then one detail will change everything.

67
00:11:02,788 --> 00:11:06,083
There you go kid, you will return to see your
fiancee, you just got your way out.

68
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:08,001
Yep, you got your way right to the court-martial.

69
00:11:08,085 --> 00:11:11,088
My sergeant, close your eyes for a change,
he already suffered enough, don't you think?

70
00:11:11,213 --> 00:11:13,006
Sergeant they may condemn him to death

71
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,007
Be understanding for a change!

72
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,008
Shut your mouth!

73
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:16,009
Come on Sergeant..

74
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,511
Shut the fuck up !

75
00:11:23,517 --> 00:11:26,603
When Mathilde and Manech made love for the
first time

76
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:30,691
Manech fell asleep with his hand over her left breast.

77
00:11:50,711 --> 00:11:53,213
Whenever he felt the wound on his hand beating,

78
00:11:53,297 --> 00:11:56,300
it was like feeling
Mathilde's heart beating.

79
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:59,887
And each beat will make him closer to her.

80
00:12:03,307 --> 00:12:06,518
If Manech were dead, Mathilde would know.

81
00:12:07,603 --> 00:12:09,813
After the news of his death,
she desperately clung

82
00:12:09,897 --> 00:12:14,484
to her intuition like a fine thread.

83
00:12:14,484 --> 00:12:17,779
Still, she never gets discouraged.

84
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:20,908
Mathilde has a cheerful disposition.

85
00:12:20,908 --> 00:12:24,912
She knows that if ever her thread
doesn't connect her to her lover

86
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:29,208
Well that's not too bad,
she still can hang herself with it.

87
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:38,300
In June of 1920
Mathilde received
a letter from a nun.

88
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:42,304
A sick man from the "Le Reim"
hospital wanted to meet her.

89
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:47,601
He was with Manech
in January 1917, on the front
of the Somme.

90
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:57,402
In August 1912, he was a good
looking man, wasn't he ?

91
00:12:57,402 --> 00:13:01,907
It is of lemon, with direct gear box.

92
00:13:02,199 --> 00:13:05,118
Please tell me what happened to Manech

93
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:08,997
In January 1917 they ordered me to
escort five

94
00:13:08,997 --> 00:13:12,000
condemned men to the front.

95
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:15,796
Was he among them ?

96
00:13:15,879 --> 00:13:17,297
Yeah.

97
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:21,802
I had to take them to the first line of
the trench.

98
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:33,105
Gendarmes waited for us with the prisoners next to
a small cemetery in ruins.

99
00:13:40,904 --> 00:13:43,907
What the fuck are you doing with those German boots?

100
00:13:43,991 --> 00:13:44,908
I am waiting.

101
00:13:44,908 --> 00:13:49,997
Waiting for what ?
To be spared by Poincare?
You can dream on Dude!

102
00:13:49,997 --> 00:13:53,792
He already signed it.
Normally I should not have been
condemned.

103
00:13:53,792 --> 00:13:56,295
I am from Corsica, you know, not French!

104
00:14:04,303 --> 00:14:07,806
Let him be. He loses a wee bit his head for

105
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:10,100
Lucky him.

106
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,317
Are you done, lieutenant?

107
00:14:20,319 --> 00:14:25,115
That soldier, He doesn't have long before
he dies, the cold will kill him.

108
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:33,707
What about Manech? ...Does the wound on his hand make
him suffer badly??

109
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:38,086
We had to amputate two fingers,
but it seemed he was doing okay.

110
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:44,092
They took them to a trench called "the
bingo twilight".

111
00:14:59,816 --> 00:15:04,780
Fucking hell. Could you make sure to kick these
useless people out of the trench on your way ??

112
00:15:04,988 --> 00:15:07,282
To kick their ass so as to come along faster?

113
00:15:07,699 --> 00:15:10,410
My orders were to deliver you
the five condemned men, I don't care about
the rest.

114
00:15:10,619 --> 00:15:13,413
Then I will tell them what my orders are...
to throw these guys from  the trench.

115
00:15:13,497 --> 00:15:18,001
and to let them die like dogs between the two
firing lines.

116
00:15:18,001 --> 00:15:22,506
Those are my fucking orders
Sergeant!

117
00:15:24,091 --> 00:15:27,594
You understand Sergeant, we have a special
tactical agreement with the Germans.

118
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:32,808
The sector is wee bit sleepy, a kick in the
ass and all the shit will explode in our faces !

119
00:15:34,184 --> 00:15:37,604
The soup guys, You are lucky it is warm.

120
00:15:46,488 --> 00:15:49,199
And what would you like to get kiddo?

121
00:15:49,992 --> 00:15:52,995
A chocolate cup and a piece of bread with honey.

122
00:15:53,203 --> 00:15:55,706
Unless I have to kill my parents: I will get that for you.

123
00:15:56,707 --> 00:15:58,917
Do you mind lieutenant?

124
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:02,880
Don't worry, he is an orphan,
but he will no doubt get you what
you want.

125
00:16:03,005 --> 00:16:08,218
He is the chief of the kitchens.

126
00:16:08,802 --> 00:16:11,889
15 minutes later, he brought everything.

127
00:16:11,889 --> 00:16:15,517
Bread with salt, honey of lavagne and...

128
00:16:16,518 --> 00:16:19,897
Cacao of Nigeria.

129
00:16:23,901 --> 00:16:25,903
Happiness

130
00:16:25,986 --> 00:16:28,322
There you go kid, do you have anyone to write to?

131
00:16:28,614 --> 00:16:29,990
Do you have a girlfriend?

132
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,992
Mathilde

133
00:16:32,993 --> 00:16:34,620
His girlfriends's name is Mathilde.

134
00:16:37,581 --> 00:16:39,708
Mathilde

135
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:43,420
I feel like her heart beats in me with Morse code.

136
00:16:45,297 --> 00:16:48,300
We are about to get married.

137
00:16:50,010 --> 00:16:54,515
They condemned us and we don't have to wait for the
end of war anymore.

138
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:59,394
I will go Home when the
execution is over.

139
00:17:08,403 --> 00:17:12,491
Maybe it is better that I don't tell you the
end.

140
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:15,619
I am lame, not stupid

141
00:17:15,702 --> 00:17:18,497
Tell me what happens.

142
00:17:19,206 --> 00:17:22,000
We opened a breach in the wire fences.

143
00:17:22,084 --> 00:17:25,504
and helped the five soldiers to fight against the cold.

144
00:17:28,298 --> 00:17:33,011
Célestin Poux gave your boyfriend one of his red wool
gloves, so that the hand was protected.

145
00:17:35,013 --> 00:17:36,515
Is it far away ??

146
00:17:36,598 --> 00:17:40,185
Less than 100 meters. Far for the grenades and
close for the artillery.

147
00:17:40,519 --> 00:17:43,188
And not to mention the gas.

148
00:17:43,313 --> 00:17:45,107
Do you think that they will be all right?

149
00:17:45,190 --> 00:17:48,902
If they don't fly in the air,
they will very likely die of hunger and cold.

150
00:17:48,986 --> 00:17:52,281
In any case the Germans will shut up for a while.

151
00:17:56,994 --> 00:18:00,414
Bastoche the carpenter has been embraced
by a corporal.

152
00:18:00,581 --> 00:18:05,085
It was obvious they knew each other before the war.

153
00:18:06,086 --> 00:18:09,214
Soon... we took them outside the trench.

154
00:18:12,217 --> 00:18:14,303
- Assholes.

155
00:18:23,312 --> 00:18:25,397
- Shit!
- Shut up!

156
00:18:28,984 --> 00:18:31,987
In September 1914, I could easily lift 70 kilos.

157
00:18:31,987 --> 00:18:35,490
Moreover I was already not in great shape like
in the past.

158
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:40,913
But that morning, in january 1917
was Manech still alive?

159
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:45,918
At the dawn, Favart shout out their names.

160
00:18:46,293 --> 00:18:49,713
All, except the farmer from Dordogne, responded.

161
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:52,090
- Bassignano?
- Present.

162
00:18:52,216 --> 00:18:54,218
- Bouquette?
- what the hell do you want?

163
00:18:55,219 --> 00:18:57,888
- Langonnet?
- Yeah, I am here.

164
00:18:58,096 --> 00:19:00,891
Man, you should hide in a better spot.

165
00:19:01,892 --> 00:19:06,104
Notre Dame? Notre Dame?

166
00:19:08,106 --> 00:19:10,817
I know nothing else.

167
00:19:11,485 --> 00:19:14,613
I retired to write my report
young lady.

168
00:19:19,284 --> 00:19:22,996
At last soldier, the English have come
to take our place, we can go.

169
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:24,998
And the subject bingo?

170
00:19:25,082 --> 00:19:26,208
What is that?

171
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:29,002
The list of the condemned signed by
Captain Favourier.

172
00:19:29,211 --> 00:19:32,214
Do I leave it there?
Nope, give it to me.

173
00:19:42,182 --> 00:19:45,018
Don't stay there like an idiot.
What are you waiting for?

174
00:19:45,018 --> 00:19:47,980
You are promoted sergeant first thing in the
morning and leave for the Bosbos.

175
00:19:48,313 --> 00:19:52,401
Even so my commander, this mission is
going away to be stuck in my throat.

176
00:19:52,609 --> 00:19:57,114
Good news, there are balsamic caramels for the
throat there.

177
00:19:57,197 --> 00:19:59,408
The caramels of the Bosbos.
We are done.

178
00:19:59,616 --> 00:20:02,995
Some months later, I had been
hurt in the Somme.

179
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:06,915
I found myself in the same ambulance as
Chardolot.

180
00:20:07,082 --> 00:20:10,002
One of the officers in "the bingo twilight".

181
00:20:10,294 --> 00:20:12,588
But he only had a few days to live.

182
00:20:14,882 --> 00:20:18,302
Eh oh, It is me Esperanza.

183
00:20:19,303 --> 00:20:21,680
Bingo twilight, you remember?

184
00:20:22,014 --> 00:20:24,600
Oh, sorry I didn't recognize you.

185
00:20:25,517 --> 00:20:27,811
Tell me, my no man's land boys...

186
00:20:27,895 --> 00:20:29,688
How did the story finish ?

187
00:20:29,688 --> 00:20:30,689
What do you think ?

188
00:20:32,107 --> 00:20:33,609
No survivor ??

189
00:20:33,609 --> 00:20:36,195
Do you feel remorse?

190
00:20:36,904 --> 00:20:38,989
You should have stayed with us in Bingo.

191
00:20:40,407 --> 00:20:43,994
I saw the capital Ms written down

192
00:20:44,286 --> 00:20:46,413
... underpants, an albatross.

193
00:20:47,414 --> 00:20:50,709
You are delirious. You have the flu.

194
00:20:51,084 --> 00:20:55,297
We threw between two lines five boys alive,
then we recovered five cold pieces of meat.

195
00:20:55,380 --> 00:21:00,093
So...

196
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:04,515
I lost my vision sergeant, but
I imagine your face.
That makes my day.

197
00:21:05,516 --> 00:21:08,602
He really spoke of capital Ms and an albatross?

198
00:21:09,895 --> 00:21:12,105
Yep ... and of underpants.

199
00:21:13,899 --> 00:21:17,486
There you go Young lady,
everything the condemned men
in Bingo ever possessed.

200
00:21:17,486 --> 00:21:20,489
They asked me to send everything to their families.

201
00:21:20,614 --> 00:21:23,408
My health didn't allow me to do it.

202
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:28,997
It is a copy of the letter of the farmer Benoît
Notre Dame to his wife.

203
00:21:29,081 --> 00:21:31,708
I sent the original one to her
when I left Bingo.

204
00:21:32,709 --> 00:21:35,212
His health is due to the gas in the lungs right?

205
00:21:36,004 --> 00:21:39,216
Nope, it is because he got the Spanish flu.

206
00:21:39,383 --> 00:21:43,804
You can notice, the death is lurking and catches
us totally by surprise.

207
00:21:46,807 --> 00:21:51,687
Mathilde, you don't have to be pissed off,
you can talk to me.

208
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:55,983
If you can't talk, just stay quiet.

209
00:21:56,984 --> 00:21:59,987
But sometimes when we start speaking, it's
when we start crying.

210
00:22:00,404 --> 00:22:03,115
And when crying
we talk about what you didn't want to

211
00:22:03,282 --> 00:22:05,909
hear, you know what I mean?

212
00:22:07,911 --> 00:22:11,290
I will not have to bear that silly face anymore.

213
00:22:40,485 --> 00:22:45,407
Petit Louis tell Vero that I will always think about
her and that it is too bad she doesn't want to

214
00:22:45,616 --> 00:22:50,996
talk to me, I met Biscotte again
and we made up. Good bye
my friend, Bastoche

215
00:22:52,998 --> 00:22:58,921
Benoît Notre Dame Number 1818
I will not be able to write again
for a while.

216
00:22:58,921 --> 00:23:01,882
Tell Berney I will pay everything by the month of March.

217
00:23:01,882 --> 00:23:03,717
He sells his installment for too much.

218
00:23:03,717 --> 00:23:05,802
You have to be careful.

219
00:23:05,802 --> 00:23:10,891
Tell my Bagtistan that I hope nothing bad will happen to him.

220
00:23:10,891 --> 00:23:14,603
I have never known such a nice person.
I love you, Benoît.

221
00:23:16,605 --> 00:23:19,900
For Tina Lombardi from Ange Bassignano.

222
00:23:58,897 --> 00:24:04,695
If the dog enters the room before they call me
for the dinner, Manech must be still alive.

223
00:24:12,703 --> 00:24:14,580
I am not hungry.

224
00:24:18,584 --> 00:24:22,796
The dinner is ready.
Come Malthide, let's go to eat.

225
00:24:23,797 --> 00:24:26,091
I'm coming.

226
00:24:26,592 --> 00:24:28,802
Mathilde was born on the first of January 1900

227
00:24:29,094 --> 00:24:31,388
That makes it very easy to determinate one's age.

228
00:24:31,597 --> 00:24:35,601
In 1903 her parents passed away in
an accident on bus 44.

229
00:24:35,601 --> 00:24:38,896
Since then Mathilde kept saying

230
00:24:39,021 --> 00:24:44,985
Late parents... late parents...

231
00:24:47,487 --> 00:24:51,617
Her Uncle Sylvain and Aunt Bénédicte
took care of her.

232
00:24:52,201 --> 00:24:57,915
Thanks to the life insurance managed by the
lawyer of her parents, Pierre Marie Rouvières.

233
00:24:58,081 --> 00:25:01,710
At five years old, Mathilde caught the polio virus.

234
00:25:01,793 --> 00:25:06,507
She stayed several months in the bed in spite of
the mustard cataplasms,

235
00:25:06,715 --> 00:25:08,091
the pendulums,

236
00:25:08,217 --> 00:25:11,887
and the infusions of shamrock with four leaves.

